    {
      "id": "1d36159f4679ca5b6a879c7fd0e15f29ebaa9489",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-02-16 17:00:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI am not sure I understand the logic behind this change at all.\n\nIf we return just open lock from open, this open lock can never be reused unless there is already a lookup lock on the client somehow. But there are a lot of cases where there is no way to get this lookup lock. E.g. when there are just opens happening, the lookup lock won't appear at all.\nNote that CR and PR lock modes don't conflict.\n\nCan you explain this some more?\n\nNote that setattr conflicting is important, because if the lock is for EXEC and you do setattr (truncate), you must flush the open first or the setattr will fail with file busy.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "dc6a2edf6b5269ef299b90625d187081401e3cbe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-02-21 17:34:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI am putting a negative review until I get some answers to remove this from my radar until then",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
